Source: ifs-kernel-updates
Maintainer: Brian T. Smith <bsmith@systemfabricworks.com>
Section: kernel
Priority: extra
Standards-Version: 3.9.8
Homepage: http://www.intel.com
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 10),
               linux-headers-4.9.0-14-amd64,
               unifdef

Package: ifs-kernel-updates-dev
Architecture: amd64
Section: libdevel
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
Conflicts: compat-rdma,
Description: Development headers for Intel HFI1 driver interface
 Development header files for Intel HFI1 driver interface. This is
 used for software that communicates directly with the HFI1 driver,
 as opposed to using an API such as PSM2 or libibverbs.

Package: kmod-ifs-kernel-updates-4.9.0-14-amd64
Architecture: amd64
Depends: linux-image-4.9.0-14-amd64,
         ${misc:Depends},
Conflicts: compat-rdma,
Replaces: compat-rdma,
Description: Updated kernel modules for Omni-Path
 Updated kernel modules for Omni-Path, compiled for kernel
 4.9.0-14-amd64.
 Includes the hfi1 driver for Omni-Path hardware and updated
 rdmavt.

Package: kmod-ifs-kernel-updates
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, kmod-ifs-kernel-updates-4.9.0-14-amd64
Description: Updated kernel modules for Omni-Path
 This is a metapackage that will depend on the latest version of the
 kernel modules for Omni-Path.
 Install this package to automatically install the latest OPA module
 when new versions of the kernel are released.
